# Simple Vectorless RAG with PageIndex + Databricks Foundation Model API

This notebook replicates the [PageIndex simple RAG cookbook](https://github.com/VectifyAI/PageIndex/blob/main/cookbook/pageindex_RAG_simple.ipynb) but uses **Databricks Foundation Model APIs** as the LLM — no OpenAI key needed.

**How it works:**
1. Upload a PDF to PageIndex → get a hierarchical tree index
2. Use a Databricks-hosted LLM to **reason over the tree** and select relevant node IDs
3. PageIndex retrieves the text for those nodes
4. The same Databricks LLM **generates the final answer** from the retrieved context

---

### Why this works with zero code changes to the LLM calls

Databricks Foundation Model APIs expose an **OpenAI-compatible endpoint**. The only two things that change:

| Setting | Original (OpenAI) | Databricks |
|---|---|---|
| `base_url` | `https://api.openai.com/v1` | `https://<your-workspace>.azuredatabricks.net/serving-endpoints` |
| `api_key` | OpenAI key | Databricks Personal Access Token |
| `model` | `gpt-4o` | endpoint name e.g. `databricks-meta-llama-3-3-70b-instruct` |

Everything else — including all PageIndex calls — stays identical.
