### 0.1 Configure credentials

**Databricks token**: Go to your workspace → top-right avatar → *User Settings* → *Developer* → *Access tokens* → *Generate new token*.

**Workspace URL**: The hostname in your browser when you are in the workspace, e.g. `https://adb-1234567890.12.azuredatabricks.net`

> 💡 **Inside a Databricks notebook?** You can skip the token and workspace URL — the `databricks-openai` SDK can auto-detect them from the cluster context. See Section 0.3b.
import os

# --- PageIndex ---
# Free API key at https://dash.pageindex.ai/api-keys
PAGEINDEX_API_KEY = os.getenv("PAGEINDEX_API_KEY", "YOUR_PAGEINDEX_API_KEY")

# --- Databricks ---
DATABRICKS_HOST  = os.getenv("DATABRICKS_HOST",  "https://<your-workspace>.azuredatabricks.net")
DATABRICKS_TOKEN = os.getenv("DATABRICKS_TOKEN", "YOUR_DATABRICKS_PAT")

# --- Model endpoint name ---
# Pay-per-token endpoints (pre-configured in every workspace, no setup needed):
#   "databricks-meta-llama-3-3-70b-instruct"   ← recommended starting point
#   "databricks-meta-llama-3-1-70b-instruct"
#   "databricks-meta-llama-3-1-405b-instruct"  ← largest / most capable
#   "databricks-llama-4-maverick"               ← latest Llama 4 (where available)
