## 6. Switching between Databricks-hosted models

Since all endpoints share the same OpenAI-compatible interface, swapping models is a one-liner.
The table below shows the main pay-per-token endpoints available in most workspaces.

| Endpoint name | Notes |
|---|---|
| `databricks-meta-llama-3-3-70b-instruct` | Best balance of speed and quality |
| `databricks-meta-llama-3-1-405b-instruct` | Highest quality open model |
| `databricks-llama-4-maverick` | Latest Llama 4 (check region availability) |
| `databricks-mistral-large-2` | Strong for multilingual & coding |
| `databricks-claude-3-7-sonnet` | Anthropic Claude (external model endpoint) |
| `databricks-gemini-2-0-flash` | Google Gemini (external model endpoint) |
| `your-provisioned-endpoint` | Any custom/fine-tuned model you deployed |
original_model = DATABRICKS_MODEL

# Try a different model — only this line changes
DATABRICKS_MODEL = "databricks-meta-llama-3-1-405b-instruct"

await pageindex_rag(
    "Summarise the main contributions of this paper in 3 bullet points.",
    doc_id,
    tree,
)

DATABRICKS_MODEL = original_model  # restore
---
## 7. Bonus — Using a custom or fine-tuned model from Unity Catalog

If your team has registered a fine-tuned model (e.g. trained on internal regulatory documents)
and deployed it via Mosaic AI Model Serving, you can use it here with no other changes:

```python
DATABRICKS_MODEL = "my-finetuned-llama-regulatory-v2"   # your serving endpoint name
await pageindex_rag("What does Article 42 say about data retention?", doc_id, tree)
```

The notebook treats every endpoint identically — the OpenAI-compatible interface is the same
whether the model is a pay-per-token foundation model or your own fine-tuned deployment.
---
## Summary

This notebook demonstrated the **same vectorless, reasoning-based RAG pipeline** as the original PageIndex cookbook, now fully powered by **Databricks Foundation Model APIs**.

**What changed from the original:**

| | Original (OpenAI) | OpenRouter version | **Databricks version** |
|---|---|---|---|
| `base_url` | `api.openai.com/v1` | `openrouter.ai/api/v1` | `<workspace>/serving-endpoints` |
| `api_key` | OpenAI key | OpenRouter key | **Databricks PAT** |
| Model string | `gpt-4.1` | `google/gemini-2.0-flash-001` | `databricks-meta-llama-3-3-70b-instruct` |
| PageIndex calls | unchanged | unchanged | **unchanged** |

**Benefits of the Databricks approach:**
- Data never leaves your Databricks workspace / cloud tenant
- Models are governed through Unity Catalog alongside your data
- Swap in your own fine-tuned models with a single endpoint name change
- AI Gateway provides rate limiting, cost tracking and audit logs across all endpoints

